%% Diagram: Kafka evolution from first commit to KRaft-only
%% Type: timeline
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
timeline
    title Kafka design evolution at and beyond LinkedIn
    2010 : First Kafka code at LinkedIn
         : ZooKeeper for coordination + offsets
    2011 : Open-sourced (Jan)
         : NetDB paper (Jun)
         : 1B msg/day at LinkedIn (Jul)
    2013 : Apache Top-Level Project (Oct 2012)
         : 0.8 - leader/follower replication (Dec)
         : "The Log" essay
    2014 : 2M writes/sec benchmark
         : Confluent founded (Sep)
         : I Heart Logs (book)
    2015 : 0.9 - offsets move to __consumer_offsets
         : New Java consumer
    2017 : 0.11 - idempotent producer + transactions
         : Exactly-once semantics
    2019 : LinkedIn at 7T msg/day
         : Brooklin open-sourced (CDC + mirroring)
    2022 : 3.3 - KRaft marked production-ready (KIP-833)
    2024 : 3.9 - tiered storage GA (KIP-405)
    2025 : 4.0 - ZooKeeper removed, KRaft only
